I'll post this here as well:

I left a message in another Blue Chart forum that said I would give codes to anyone who could seed the European data, any Asian data, Middle Eastern/Africa data, Pac Blue chart, and USA Blue Chart data.  I asked several months ago, but never got the data.

I can generate codes for OLDER devices.  Older means things like the 60cs and so forth, as well as e-map and others.  I need your Unit ID.  Without it, the code is worthless.

Anyone willing to seed the above info for a good period of time can get ONE free unlock code/mapset seeded.  If you seed them all, then you get all the codes.  However, DO NOT LEAVE MESSAGES HERE ASKING FOR CODES.  I don't check this place for mail but once in a blue moon.  I logged in a found several code requests in my mailbox from april when I posted my last message.  Instead, seed the info, and let me know you've seeded it at:

roboknight+unlockcode at gmail dot com

(use that whole first piece before the "at") ...

I'm not in the business of putting Garmin out of business.  So I won't give away any free unlock codes.  I know Garmin's price structure sucks.  I've got friends who've been burned by it.  I also think it is stupid that they don't let you "replace" your GPS by turning in your old one for an unlock code for a new one for free... But, that's the way they want to do it and I don't plan to tell them their way of doing business is wrong by giving away free codes.  So unless you can seed the data, don't ask for a code.
Well, got the data I needed.  Thanks a bunch.  I did give out a few free codes anyway, but in the immortal words of Dennis Miller:  "I am outta here."
